In 2013 he was murdered by a member of the far-right political party Golden Dawn.

Paul Frappier (May 8, 1977 – February 11, 2011), better known by his stage name Bad News Brown, was a Canadian musician, and hip hop MC from Little Burgundy, Montreal, Canada. He was murdered in 2011.

Moss was known for his trend setting and innovative abilities in music producing and broadcasting as well as his philosophy of "peace in the hood" and non-violence in the community. He was shot and killed on September 10, 2001.

Randy Walker (August 21, 1968 – November 30, 1995), better known by his stage name Stretch, was an American rapper and record producer. He was a member of the Live Squad with his brother Majesty. On November 30, 1995, Stretch was murdered.

Charles Edward Hicks Jr. (July 6, 1973 – December 16, 1993), also known by his stage name Charizma, was an MC from Milpitas, California, United States.
